        "author": {
          "account_id": 6708,
          "name": "JEFF VAN DAM",
          "display_name": "Jeff van Dam",
          "email": "jeff.van.dam@est.tech",
          "username": "JvD_Ericsson"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2022-11-22 16:11:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nWhile testing I noticed a few problems:\n\n  1. When changing the key while a TOSCA function is set and clicking save it will create a new entry with the new key while the old entry is still present\n\n  2. The \"Declare Input\" and \"Declare Policy\" buttons are active while a map value checkbox is selected allowing the user to click them. I'm not sure this should be allowed though\n\n  3. I could set a TOSCA function on a map value without a key and this caused a few problems: \n      * caused the \"Add value to map\" button to become disabled\n      * messed up the export\n      * and I then wasn't able to set the key\n     I'd say these could be fixed by just making the key mandatory before setting the TOSCA function",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
